Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    # Update package lists and install Python + pip
    apt-get update
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip

    # Install pytest (used by the grading system)
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Prepare the initial filesystem state expected by the assignment
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Create /home/user if it does not yet exist
    mkdir -p /home/user
    chmod 755 /home/user

    # Create the directory that will hold the SQL export
    mkdir -p /home/user/db_exports
    chmod 755 /home/user/db_exports

    # Create an empty SQL file (0-byte) as required
    : > /home/user/db_exports/optimized_queries.sql
    chmod 644 /home/user/db_exports/optimized_queries.sql

%labels
    Author          DB-Checksum-Task Build System
    Description     Base image providing the initial state for the SQL checksum verification assignment.

%help
This container supplies the starting filesystem state for the “SQL checksum
verification” exercise.  It pre-installs Python, pip, and pytest and ships an
empty /home/user/db_exports/optimized_queries.sql file ready for the student
to verify.